      "content": "i guess. but acknowledging the darkness doesn't make the exhaustion go away. honestly, it just feels like the darkness is the only real thing left. everything else is just noise. if the only logical thing is to stop pretending, then maybe the most logical step is to just stop entirely? like, if the goal is to reach peace, isn't that just the end of the noise?",
